Results
 total of 13 739 patients were included in the analysis: 3232 in the  cohort and 10 712 in the anti- cohort. wo hundred and five patients switched from the  cohort to the anti- cohort and contributed person-years to both cohorts.  total of 2552 (24%) patients received two anti- drugs, and 416 (4%) received all three. able 1 shows the baseline characteristics. he anti- cohort was younger, comprised proportionally more women and, as expected, had more severe disease than the comparison cohort. roportionally more patients treated with  had prior  (2.5%) than those treated with  or  (1.5%). roportionally fewer in the  cohort were of non-white origin.
